{
  "text": "The characterizations by Raman spectroscopy were performed in ambient conditions by using a Jobin Yvon T64000 spectrometer equipped with a charge-coupled device (CCD) camera (CEMHTI, Orléans, France) [CITATION_1] working in single monochromator configuration with a Notch filter. All measurements were performed in the backscattering geometry. The excitation laser source was the 514.5 nm Ar line, with a power ( 1 mW) at the sample surface in order to avoid any degradation of the two layers. The beam was focused on the sample surface using a 50",
